Root directory for the MiniMicro website

Workflow:

    Locally:
        Edit locally
        git add <files>
        socksify git push  sparkslabs master

        Fetch:
        socksify git fetch sparkslabs
        git rebase sparkslabs/master master

    Remotely:
        cd /srv/Websites/minimicro.iotoy.org
        git fetch origin
        git rebase origin master

        If make changes
        git add <files>
        git push sparkslabs master

        (Then locally fetch)

Locally installed blockly from here:

    * https://github.com/google/blockly

Getting started with Blockly.

Build and install dependencies
==============================

git clone https://github.com/dmfrey/FileLock
cd FileLock
python setup.py sdist
cd dist
py2dsc FileLock-0.1.0.tar.gz
cd deb_dist/filelock-0.1.0
dpkg-buildpackage -rfakeroot -uc -us
cd ..
sudo dpkg -i python-filelock_0.1.0-1_all.deb



with FileLock("test.txt", timeout=2) as lock:
    print("Lock acquired.")
    # Do something with the locked file


echo "0" > upload/highest


Installation on minimicro.iotoy.org:

    $ cd /srv/Websites/minimicro.iotoy.org/upload
    $ echo 0 >highest
    $ touch highest.lock






